---
// One idea: fresh eyes don't see more facts — they look at the tangle until the
// few forces that actually move it surface as a shape.
---
<svg viewBox="0 0 560 200" role="img" aria-labelledby="fe-t">
  <title id="fe-t">On the left, a dense scribbled tangle of noise. An arrow of patient looking resolves it, on the right, into a clean simple shape — two or three lines and a focal point, the few forces that move the whole.</title>
  <!-- the tangle -->
  <path class="ink hair" d="M50 60 C 90 40, 70 100, 110 90 C 150 80, 120 130, 90 120 C 50 108, 100 150, 140 130 C 170 116, 130 70, 96 84 C 64 96, 110 56, 80 66" opacity="0.7" />
  <text class="hand-label" x="60" y="176" font-size="13" opacity="0.7">the tangle</text>
  <!-- looking resolves it -->
  <path class="ink hair" d="M190 100 C 230 98, 258 100, 288 102" stroke-dasharray="2 6" stroke="var(--poppy)" />
  <text class="hand-label hand-label--accent" x="196" y="88" font-size="13">looked at, freshly</text>
  <!-- the shape: few forces -->
  <path class="ink spine" d="M330 140 C 380 96, 440 96, 490 60" />
  <path class="ink block" d="M410 130 C 430 108, 460 110, 470 90" />
  <circle class="port-fill" cx="440" cy="98" r="4" />
  <text class="hand-label hand-label--accent" x="360" y="176" font-size="13">the shape — the few forces</text>
</svg>
